entry.content: "To be successful in politics...women shave off so much of the edges of their personality until basically they're a man." "The 2023 that I want to live in, I want people to be able to be their full selves. I want to live in a world where wearing a ball gown or wearing a bikini doesn't negate your ability to be a good political staffer." said Alisha Aitken-Ratburn, author of 'The Villain Edit', 3x Bachelor contestant and former Labor staffer, at our Politics in the Pub event.
